      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. Let's get straight to the point. The indemnification clause in the NDA you're referring to means that you, as the Recipient, agree to cover all costs, damages, and expenses that the Disclosing Party might incur as a result of your breach of the agreement or any misrepresentations you make. This includes legal fees, which can be substantial depending on the complexity of the case and the amount of work required to resolve it.\n\n\"Reasonable attorneys' fees\" is a term that can vary widely based on the jurisdiction and the specifics of the case. In some cases, these fees could be a few thousand dollars, while in others, they could run into tens of thousands or even more, especially if the case goes to trial or requires extensive legal work. The exact amount would typically be determined by the court or agreed upon by the parties involved.\n\nTo mitigate your risk, it's important to carefully review the terms of the NDA and consult with a legal professional who can provide guidance based on the specific details of your situation. They can help you understand the potential financial implications and advise you on how to proceed to minimize your exposure.",
